\begin_layout Section

Product functions:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	This system would allow different user types to navigate around the University
 of Pretoria's main campus grounds.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	This system would include three different types of users, namely: a student;
 a staff member and a visitor.
 All three
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	users of the system would be able search for specific buildings and receive
 a guided path from their current position 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	to the searched area.
 The student and staff member users would both be able to search for events
 happening on 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	the main campus grounds and be able to save their searched areas for quick
 searches in future use.
 The system
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	will also have restricted areas so as not to lead users through restricted
 areas.
 Popular areas, such as the food court,
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	will be ready to choose options making them easier and quicker to find.
 Emergency gathering areas will also be highlighted
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	and highly visible to all users.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\begin_layout Section

User characteristics:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	There will be three user types, the student; the staff member and the visitor.
 All users will be able to access
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	the basic functionalities of the system.
 They will be all be able to search for a location on the main campus 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	of University of Pretoria.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	A visitor user will be limited to searching for their conference or building
 that they
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	require as the rest of the functionality will be of no interest to them.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	The student user will have access to basic finctionality of the system
 but will reeive push notifications of special events on
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	campus such as a conference on the field of study or a club performing
 a showcase.
 This functionality will be 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	customizable for each user to choose the interests.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	The staff member user will receive basic access to the system along with
 routes to restricted areas, upcoming conference
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	locations and special events on campus.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\end_layout

\begin_layout Section

Constraints:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	The accuracy of this system will be limited as there is not Wi-Fi signal
 across the entire main campus.
 Most of the
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	system's functionalities will be unavailable without internet access for
 the user.
 This is particularily problematic
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	near the gates of the campus as the user will have to use their own internet
 connections.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	To detect the traffic density on campus, most people on campus will have
 to be connected and their location trcked.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	This becomes problematic when users are not connected as the traffic density
 will become inaccurate.
 Another potential
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	problem with this is the strain the users will put on the system when many
 users are on campus simultaneously.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	This system will also rely on the University of Pretoia's calendar which
 require the calendar be up to date constantly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	It will also require the organisers of conferences and showcases to input
 their respective events so that they can be showed 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	on the system.
 The problem here lies in that organisers may not input their events and
 so users will not becoe aware
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph

	of them.
\end_layout

